阿尔伯特·艾利斯小心地说明，REBT 与无神论无关，<!-- note that many skilled REBT 从业者是宗教信徒，including some who are ordained ministers. While Ellis maintained his stance, proposing that thoughtful, probabilistic atheism is likely the most emotionally healthy approach to life, he acknowledged and agreed with survey evidence suggesting that belief in a loving God is also  psychologically healthy. Based on this later approach to religion, he co-authored a book describing principles for integrating religious material and beliefs with REBT during treatment of religious clients, ''Counseling and Psychotherapy with Religious Persons: A Rational Emotive Behavior Therapy Approach''. -->

== 晚年 ==
2004年，阿尔伯特·艾利斯罹患严重的肠炎，<!-- which led to hospitalization and the removal of his large intestine. He returned to work after a few months of being nursed back to health by Debbie Joffe, his assistant, who later became his wife.

